citation: Proclamation under the Cat Management Amendment Act 2020 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Cat Management Amendment Act 2020

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Cat Management Amendment Act 2020 â€“

        (a) fix 1 March 2021 as the day on which the provisions of that Act, other than sections 9 , 10 , 11 , 12 , 13 , 21 , 22 and 23 , commence; and
        (b) fix 1 March 2022 as the day on which sections 9 , 10 , 11 , 12 , 13 , 21 , 22 and 23 of that Act commence.
27 January 2021

C. WARNER

Governor

By Her Excellency's Command,

GUY BARNETT

Minister for Primary Industries and Water

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 3 February 2021

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Primary Industries, Parks, Water and Environment.
